		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Nope, because there's no NES MMC3 cart with both CHR-RAM and WRAM.  Which is what kyuusaku meant by an equivalent cart.  You have to modify a CHR-ROM board to support CHR-RAM (requires adding a pin to the edge connector + rewiring).

		

